First the `ex5b_supplier_exist` function. To find out if a `SUPPLIER_ID` exists, you need to query the `SUPPLIER` database table, not the `PRODUCT` table. Also, no need to define a cursor, a simple `count(*)` query will suffice and also avoids the `NO_DATA_FOUND` exception if the supplied `SUPPLIER_ID` does not exist...

    create or replace function ex5b_supplier_exist(sid supplier.supplier_id%type)
    return boolean
    is
      l_count  pls_integer;
    begin
      select count(*)
        into l_count
        from supplier
       where supplier_id = sid;
      return l_count &gt; 0;
    end ex5b_supplier_exist;

Now the `ex5b_supplier_update` procedure. Since you are removing a `SUPPLIER_ID`, you need to first update any database tables that reference that ID. If you don&#39;t, you will get an error...

&gt;ORA-02292: integrity constraint (PRODUCT_FK) violated - child record found

Hence procedure `ex5b_supplier_update` must first update tables `PRODUCT` and `PURCHASE_ORDER` since they both may contain rows with the `SUPPLIER_ID` you are about to delete from the `SUPPLIER` table.

    create or replace procedure ex5b_supplier_update(del_supp_id supplier.supplier_id%type
                                                    ,upd_supp_id supplier.supplier_id%type)
    as
    begin
      if ex5b_supplier_exist(del_supp_id) and ex5b_supplier_exist(upd_supp_id) then
        update product
           set supplier_id = upd_supp_id
         where supplier_id = del_supp_id;
      --
        update purchase_order
           set supplier_id = upd_supp_id
         where supplier_id = del_supp_id;
      --
        delete from supplier
         where supplier_id = del_supp_id;
      --
        dbms_output.put_line(&#39;update successful&#39;);
      else
        dbms_output.put_line(&#39;invalid suppliers. run the program unit again&#39;);
      end if;
    end ex5b_supplier_update;

